   "source": [
    "visit_probs_no_teleport = estimate_visit_probabilities(\n",
    "    g_pr,\n",
    "    num_steps=250000,\n",
    "    burn_in=10000\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "indeg = np.array(g_pr.degree(mode=\"in\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.scatter(indeg, visit_probs_no_teleport)\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"In-degree\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Visit probability\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We created the directed network as described and estimated the visit probability of each node using a long random walk. From the plot, the visit probability is clearly related to node degree, especially in-degree. Nodes with higher in-degree tend to have higher visit probability, because they have more incoming edges and are more likely to be reached by the random walker. So overall, there is a positive relationship between visit probability and node degree."
   ]
  },
