  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "When we add teleportation with α = 0.2, the relationship between visit probability and degree is still positive, but it becomes weaker. This is because teleportation gives the walker a chance to jump to any node, not just follow edges. As a result, even low-degree nodes can be visited, and the distribution becomes less concentrated on high-degree nodes. So increasing α makes the visit probabilities more balanced and reduces the dominance of hubs."
   ]
